label.value: Ampulla of Vater Cancer by AJCC v7 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of ampulla of Vater cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer, 7th edition.

label.value: Ampulla of Vater Cancer by AJCC v8 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of ampulla of Vater cancer according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer, 8th edition. This staging system does not apply to well-differentiated neuroendocrine (carcinoid) tumors but does apply to high-grade neuroendocrine carcinomas, such as small cell carcinoma and large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Stage 0 Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage 0 includes: Tis, N0, M0. Tis: Carcinoma in situ. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage I Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage I includes: IA: (T1a, N0, M0); IB: (T1b, N0, M0); (T2, N0, M0). T1a: Tumor limited to ampulla of Vater or sphincter of Oddi. T1b: Tumor invading beyond the sphincter of Oddi (perisphincteric invasion) and/or into the duodenal submucosa. T2: Tumor invading into the muscularis propria of the duodenum. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IA Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IA includes: T1a, N0, M0. T1a: Tumor limited to ampulla of Vater or sphincter of Oddi. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IB Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IB includes: (T1b, N0, M0); (T2, N0, M0). T1b: Tumor invading beyond the sphincter of Oddi (perisphincteric invasion) and/or into the duodenal submucosa. T2: Tumor invading into the muscularis propria of the duodenum. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage II Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage II includes: IIA: T3a, N0, M0; IIB: T3b, N0, M0. T3a: Tumor directly invading the pancreas (up to 0.5 cm). T3b: Tumor extending more than 0.5 cm into the pancreas, or extending into peripancreatic tissue or duodenal serosa without involvement of the celiac axis or superior mesenteric artery. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)
A chromosome band present on 6p

label.value: Stage IIA Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIA includes: T3a, N0, M0. T3a: Tumor directly invading the pancreas (up to 0.5 cm). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIB Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIB includes: T3b, N0, M0. T3b: Tumor extending more than 0.5 cm into the pancreas, or extending into peripancreatic tissue or duodenal serosa without involvement of the celiac axis or superior mesenteric artery. N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage III Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage III includes: IIIA: (T1a, N1, M0); (T1b, N1, M0); (T2, N1, M0); (T3a, N1, M0); (T3b, N1, M0); IIIB: (T4, Any N, M0); (Any T, N2, M0). T1a: Tumor limited to ampulla of Vater or sphincter of Oddi. T1b: Tumor invading beyond the sphincter of Oddi (perisphincteric invasion) and/or into the duodenal submucosa. T2: Tumor invading into the muscularis propria of the duodenum. T3a: Tumor directly invading the pancreas (up to 0.5 cm). T3b: Tumor extending more than 0.5 cm into the pancreas, or extending into peripancreatic tissue or duodenal serosa without involvement of the celiac axis or superior mesenteric artery. T4: Tumor involving the celiac axis, superior mesenteric artery, and/or common hepatic artery, irrespective of size. N1: Metastasis to one to three regional lymph nodes. N2: Metastasis to four or more regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIA Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: (T1a, N1, M0); (T1b, N1, M0); (T2, N1, M0); (T3a, N1, M0); (T3b, N1, M0). T1a: Tumor limited to ampulla of Vater or sphincter of Oddi. T1b: Tumor invading beyond the sphincter of Oddi (perisphincteric invasion) and/or into the duodenal submucosa. T2: Tumor invading into the muscularis propria of the duodenum. T3a: Tumor directly invading the pancreas (up to 0.5 cm). T3b: Tumor extending more than 0.5 cm into the pancreas, or extending into peripancreatic tissue or duodenal serosa without involvement of the celiac axis or superior mesenteric artery. N1: Metastasis to one to three regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IIIB Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IIIB includes: (T4, Any N, M0); (Any T, N2, M0). T4: Tumor involving the celiac axis, superior mesenteric artery, and/or common hepatic artery, irrespective of size. N2: Metastasis to four or more regional lymph nodes. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Stage IV Ampulla of Vater Cancer AJCC v8

value.value: Stage IV includes: Any T, Any N, M1. M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 8th ed.)

label.value: Chewable Gel Dosage Form

value.value: A formed or molded oral gel dosage form that maintains its shape, is elastic, and yields to mastication.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer TNM Finding v8

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system. This classification applies to pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma, acinar cell carcinoma, intraductal papillary mucinous neoplasm with associated invasive carcinoma, intraductal tubulopapillary neoplasm with associated invasive carcinoma, colloid carcinoma, mucinous cystic neoplasm with associated invasive carcinoma, solid pseudopapillary neoplasm, large cell neuroendocrine carcinoma, small cell neuroendocrine carcinoma, and pancreatoblastoma. Well-differentiated neuroendocrine tumors are not staged using this staging system. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Clinical TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.
A chromosome band present on 11p

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer cM0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer cM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pTX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with no evidence of primary tumor. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pTis TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. This includes high-grade pancreatic intraepithelial neoplasia (PanIn-3), intraductal papillary mucinous neoplasm with high-grade dysplasia, intraductal tubulopapillary neoplasm with high-grade dysplasia, and mucinous cystic neoplasm with high-grade dysplasia. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor measuring 2 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)
A chromosome band present on 9p

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT1a TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor measuring 0.5 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT1b TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor measuring more than 0.5 cm and less than 1 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT1c TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor measuring 1-2 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor measuring more than 2 cm and 4 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor measuring more than 4 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pT4 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with tumor involving the celiac axis, superior mesenteric artery, and/or common hepatic artery, regardless of size. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v8

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of exocrine pancreatic cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v8 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pNX TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with no metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with metastasis in one to three regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: Recombinant Inhibin B

value.value: A recombinant therapeutic agent which is chemically identical to or similar to an endogenous glycoprotein which inhibits pituitary production of follicle-stimulating hormone (FSH).  Produced and secreted by the testis or ovarian follicle, endogenous inhibin B contributes to the control of gametogenesis, embryonic and fetal development, and hematopoiesis. (NCI04)
A chromosome band present on 14q

label.value: Exocrine Pancreatic Cancer pN2 TNM Finding v8

value.value: Exocrine pancreatic cancer with metastasis in four or more regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 8th Ed.)

label.value: BCL6 Gene Translocation

value.value: A cytogenetic abnormality that refers to any translocation involving the BCL6 gene.

label.value: Pancreatic Cancer by AJCC v6 and v7 Stage

value.value: A term that refers to the staging of exocrine and endocrine pancreatic cancer including well-differentiated neuroendocrine tumors according to the American Joint Committee on Cancer, 6th and 7th editions.

label.value: Have Aches in Joints and/or Muscles

value.value: A question about whether an individual has aches in joints and/or muscles.

label.value: Have a Lot of Pain

value.value: A question about whether an individual has a lot of pain.

label.value: Become Nauseated During Medical Treatments

value.value: A question about whether an individual becomes nauseated during medical treatments.

label.value: Food Does Not Taste Good

value.value: A question about whether food does not taste very good to an individual.

label.value: Become Nauseated While Thinking About Medical Treatments

value.value: A question about whether an individual becomes nauseated while thinking about medical treatments.
